🔹 Step 1: Open Jenkins Dashboard

Open browser and visit:

http://localhost:8080

Login using Jenkins credentials.

🔹 Step 2: Create New Project

From Jenkins Dashboard:

Click:

New Item

Enter:

Item Name → CI-Pipeline

Select:

Freestyle Project

Click:

OK
🔹 Step 3: Configure Source Code Management (Git Integration)

Scroll to:

Source Code Management

Select:

Git

Enter Repository URL:

https://github.com/username/project.git

Specify branch name:

main
🔹 Step 4: Configure Build Tool (Maven Integration)

Scroll to:

Build

Click:

Add Build Step → Invoke top-level Maven targets

In Goals field enter:

clean install

This command:

Cleans old build files
Compiles source code
Runs tests
Creates build artifact

Click:

Advanced

Enter:

pom.xml

to read the Maven configuration file.

🔹 Optional: Gradle Integration

Instead of Maven:

Choose:

Invoke Gradle Script

Enter Gradle task:

build
🔹 Step 5: Save the Project

Click:

Save
🔹 Step 6: Run CI Pipeline

From Jenkins Dashboard:

Click:

Build Now

Jenkins starts the build process.

🔹 Step 7: View Console Output

Click:

Build #1

Then click:

Console Output
